g.text: aTheeffect of hepatic impairment on the pharmacokinetics of deutetrabenazineand its primary metabolites has not been investigated. In a clinical study conducted with tetrabenazine, a non-deuterated version of deutetrabenazine, there was a large increase in exposure to tetrabenazine and its active metabolites in patients with hepatic impairment. The clinical significance of this increased exposure has not been assessed, but because of concerns for a greaterrisk for serious adverse reactions, the use of deutetrabenazinein patients with hepatic impairment is not recommended.4
